The paper proposes a precoding scheme for downlink large-scale multiuser MIMO systems, which involves utilizing channel state information (CSI) and mitigating interference. This falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) categories. The paper also discusses the computational complexity of the proposed scheme, which could be relevant to the systems and control (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. Finally, the paper deals with multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) systems, which could be relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) category.
